notes.note: Rep from Taylor Auto Mall called to inquire about coverage for rear differential leak. Asked where it is leaking, informed me that the differential has a hole in the side of it and that it is cracked all the way around. Told her to submit an estimate with a bunch of pictures of the rear diff, and also that is is unlikely that we will cover it as those circumstances only happen due to exterior damage. M.P.
notes.content: Rep from Taylor Auto Mall called to inquire about coverage for rear differential leak. Asked where it is leaking, informed me that the differential has a hole in the side of it and that it is cracked all the way around. Told her to submit an estimate with a bunch of pictures of the rear diff, and also that is is unlikely that we will cover it as those circumstances only happen due to exterior damage. M.P.

notes.note: Rec'd picture and estimate from rep at Taylor Auto Mall. Clear hole in side of differential, and can faintly see crack going all the way around. Did not like the fact that the rep tried to misrepresent this as a "leak" when the diff is cracked/has a hole blown in the side of it. Researched and found bulletin online for this concern that states that internal damage can result from corrosion to the rear differential clutch control module, or a crack/hole in diff can be a result of corrosion to the differential housing, causing fluid loss and potentially the diff to split. Turned down claim, contract does not cover corrosion. M.P.
